Symptoms:
1. Lateral floating;
2. Opening mouth and calling;
3. Refusal to eat or drink;
4. Bubbles at the corners of the mouth.
Treatment Methods:
1. For those who eat: Place the turtle in a small container and sprinkle half an amoxicillin capsule on the food;
2. For those who refuse to eat: Mix half an amoxicillin capsule with water for a 30-minute medicated bath once a day.
Causes:
1. Placed in an air-conditioned room; (temperature difference)
2. Placed on the balcony without covering; (temperature difference)
3. Large temperature difference between old and new water during water change.
Warm Tips:
1. Pay attention to temperature difference when changing water;
2. Do not place turtles in air-conditioned rooms;
3. Pay attention to temperature difference on the balcony, cover if necessary;
